				<p><span class="red">DISORDER</span> IS A COLLECTION BASED ON THE IDEA OF NEUTRALITY AND RAW MINIMALISM, WITH THE PURPOSE OF CREATING CLOTHES THAT CAN SOMEHOW BE COMPARED TO PIECE OF ART BY THEIR UNIQUENESS. </p>
				<p>EVERYDAY LOOKS ARE REINVENTED AND RESHAPED TO FIT NEW TYPES OF IDENTITY. <span class="red">DISORDER</span> IS MEANT TO FREE PEOPLE FROM THE CHAINS OF SOCIETY AND ENABLE THEM TO SHOW WHO THEY TRULY ARE. THIS COLLECTION ENHANCES A PARTICULAR ATTITUDE RATHER THAN A SPECIFIC GENDER, GIVING AN INIMITABLE TASTE TO EVERY GARMENT JUST AS THE PAINTER DOES WITH A CANVAS. </p>
				<p>THE JAPANESE CANVAS IS THE MAIN FABRIC CHOSEN FOR <span class="red">DISORDER</span>, AS A REMINDER NOT ONLY OF ART BUT ALSO OF ITS ORIGINAL OFF-WHITE COLOUR, CREATING A SENSE OF NEUTRALITY. <span class="red">DISORDER</span> TRANSGRESSES RULES BY CREATING CONFUSION AND ERASING STEREOTYPES ASSOCIATED WITH THE SOCIETAL DEFINITION OF GENDER.
				<p><span class="red">DISORDER</span> IS THE FIRST EXPRESSION OF <span class="red">GNDR</span>.</p>
